  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study tested the hypothesis that yoga practice can improve respiratory function in the
      elderly.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Maximal inspiratory and expiratory pressure (IPmax and EPmax) were assessed by a
      manovacuometer and tidal volume (VT), vital capacity (VC) and minute ventilation (VE) were
      assessed by a ventilometer. The yoga program comprised 70 min sessions, 3 times/week during
      12 weeks.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
